Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Shale Gas Processing Equipment Market

The shale gas processing equipment market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 5.50% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on shale gas processing equipment market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the market’s growth. The commercial exploitation of the shale gas reserves is escalating the growth of shale gas processing equipment market.

Shale gas processing equipment refers to equipment used in the processing of shale gas. The most common equipment categorized under shale gas processing equipment are electrical machinery, compressors and pumps, internal combustion engines, heat exchangers and measuring and controlling devices among others. Other equipment seen is injection systems, separators and filters, storage tanks and hydrator/glycol dehydrator. The equipment are used in the midstream phase of the oil and gas during the processing, refining and treating of shale gas before being transported to commercial usage. These are known to be high power equipment utilized in several processes including pyrolysis, distillation, reheating, chemical treatment and cracking.

The rise in the demand of energy across the globe pushing companies to explore unconventional fuel reserves and the increasing rate of natural gas exploration and development activities, acting as the major factors for the shale gas processing equipment market. The growth in environmental concerns leading consumer to shift their preference towards natural gas over conventional energy sources and the rise in the investment in the exploration and production activities by government and energy companies to seek unexplored unconventional reserves accelerate the shale gas processing equipment market growth. The rise in popularity of shale gas among other gases owning to its low carbon emissions and higher calorific value and the upcoming natural pipeline projects across various regions due to the heterogeneous unconventional fuel reserve distribution influences the shale gas processing equipment market. Additionally, cost-effective unconventional drilling techniques, energy security offered by the domestic supply of natural gas and the rise in natural gas price positively affect the shale gas processing equipment market. Furthermore, technological advancement for efficient unconventional drilling techniques and expansion of shale gas infrastructure extend profitable opportunities to the shale gas processing equipment market players in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

On the other hand, contamination issues of shale fracturing, water availability and the implementation of strict government regulations associated with the shale gas processing are the factors expected to obstruct the shale gas processing equipment market growth. The health and environmental impacts of fracking chemicals and public opposition to shale fracturing application are projected to challenge the shale gas processing equipment market in the forecast period of 2021-2028.

